20 (b) Prior to permitting the execution of any electronic bond, the provider
21 shall verify that the agent seeking to post the bond is listed in the approved
22 agent registry for the parish in which the bond is to be posted. The provider
23 shall deny electronic bond access to any agent who does not appear in the
24 applicable registry.
25 (c) The sheriff shall provide the electronic bond provider with timely
26 notice of any additions to or removals from the approved registry.
27 (5) When an electronic bond is used, all of the following procedures shall
28 be followed:
29 (a) The electronic bond provider shall implement multi-factor
30 authentication for each individual bond posting transaction, which shall include
31 at a minimum both of the following:
32 (i) Facial recognition liveness verification linked to the identity of the
33 approved licensed agent executing the bond.
34 (ii) A secondary authentication factor independent of the agent's account
35 login credentials.
36 (b) The electronic bond provider shall ensure that the authentication
37 required by Subparagraph (a) of this Paragraph is performed personally by the
38 approved agent of record at the time of each individual bond posting. The
39 provider shall not permit the use of shared login credentials, shared
40 authentication devices or factors, or proxy authentication by any person other
41 than the approved agent of record.
42 (c) The approving sheriff may, as a condition of authorizing electronic
43 bond posting within the parish, require the electronic bond provider to
44 incorporate a geographic restriction, including a geofence, limiting electronic
45 bond posting to a defined geographic area within or proximate to the parish.
