4 Section 2. R.S. 22:822(A) is hereby amended and reenacted to read as follows:
5 §822. Criminal bail bond annual license fee
6 A.(1) On premiums for all commercial surety underwriters who write
7 criminal bail bonds in the state of Louisiana, there shall be a fee equal to two dollars
8 for each one hundred dollars worth of liability underwritten by the commercial
9 surety. Except as authorized under the provisions of R.S. 13:718(I)(2), this shall be
10 the exclusive fee or tax on any criminal bail bond premium, including thereto
11 premium taxes owed. In furtherance of the payment of this premium fee all
12 commercial surety underwriters underwriting criminal bail bonds in the state of
13 Louisiana shall, upon submitting the appearance bond and their power of attorney,
14 simultaneously pay to the sheriff of the parish, a fee of two dollars for each one
15 hundred dollars worth of liability on the bail bond being presented for the release of
16 a person on bail. Failure to pay the fee shall prevent the sheriff from accepting the
17 appearance bond and power of attorney. The sheriff may receive the fee by check,
18 or cash, or automated clearing house (ACH) and shall only accept it only from the
19 surety or the agent of the surety.
20 (2)(a) When an electronic bond is posted pursuant to Code of Criminal
21 Procedure Article 328, the sheriff shall accept payment of the fee by ACH
22 electronic funds transfer, and a licensed bail bond producer may collect from
23 the defendant, principal, or indemnitor any fees associated with the posting of
24 an electronic bond that are authorized by law, including but not limited to
25 platform access fees, transaction fees, and ACH processing fees.
26 (b) The fees shall not exceed the actual cost charged to the producer by
27 the electronic bond provider.
28 (c) In the event a surety or agent of the surety presents payment of the fee by
29 an instrument which is returned for insufficient funds, the agent or the agent of the
30 surety shall be prevented from presenting the appearance bonds with their power of
31 attorney attached until the outstanding fees are paid to the sheriff.
